  "text": "[12] Natural remanent magnetizations (NRMs) were determined for several samples from the survey area using a 2-G cryogenic magnetometer. Differential magnetic crystal growth due to different rates of cooling can lead to differences in NRM measurements, depending on distance from the glassy margin [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ]. All samples were thus cut radially to the outermost nonglassy part, and subsamples measured from within the crystalline matrix, at distances of 1 -5 cm from the glassy margin. The mean NRM and standard deviation of these samples is shown in Table 1 . The average magnetization of samples from the youngest flows within the three survey areas (17°28 0 S, 18°14 0 S, and 18°37 0 S) was always close to a mean value of 20 A/m.",
